    "en": "Study on the International Communication Paths of Jingchu ICH Cultural and Creative Products Represented by Jingzhou Folk Embroidery",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": null,
    "preview_source": "tier7-ingest-v0.2",
    "summary": "(ICH)within the scenario of the alignment development between the Cultural Power Strategy and \"Belt and Road\", innovating ICH creative products as key vehicles for the global circulation of intangible cultural heritages deserves extensive efforts to improve China's international cultural influence. Jingzhou folk embroidery is taken as an exemplary case for this research project. The current study delves into Jingzhou folk embroidery by mainly observing the situation and problems of its present international communication process, and points out its shortcomings in several aspects like limited content, low degree of digitalization, and lack of human resources. A lot of advice is given through consultation with experts from various aspects under the context of cultural inheritance and modern"
